stylometry: Fixed cost models and set covering models have to deal with using only what materials or time is allocated to us.  These problems are trying to show how much you can produce or use efficiently with the constraints entered.  This is important because everything will have limits, and we need to know how to use those limits to their full extent.  Ex - If you have to produce tables and chairs with x and y costs for each and z to spend overall.  What is the most efficient way to do so?
